        <briefdescription>
<para>Compute statistics asynchronously. </para>
        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para>Launches GPU kernels to compute moments and counts. Results are written to pinned host memory asynchronously.</para>
<para><parameterlist kind="param"><parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>particles</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>Particle positions (device pointers) </para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
<parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>grid</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>Grid descriptor (for domain size in unwrap) </para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
<parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>config</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>Computation configuration </para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
<parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>stream</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>CUDA stream for async execution</para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
</parameterlist>
<simplesect kind="return"><para>cudaSuccess on launch success, error code otherwise</para>
</simplesect>
<simplesect kind="note"><para>Does NOT synchronize. Caller must synchronize stream before calling <ref refid="classpar2_1_1StatsComputer_1a13c5539a0d595310bd06eabc5922876b" kindref="member">fetch_result()</ref>.</para>
</simplesect>
<simplesect kind="warning"><para>If particles.n &gt; max_particles, returns cudaErrorInvalidValue. </para>
</simplesect>
</para>
